\begin_inset Formula $\sim5$\, AU

\end_inset 

.
 The parameters used for the model fit are: 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{\mathrm{max}}=22000\,\mathrm{K}$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{\mathrm{wind}}=8000\,\mathrm{K}$
\end_inset 

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{M}_{\mathrm{acc}}=1.1\times10^{-8}\,\mathrm{M_{\sun}\, yr^{-1}}$
\end_inset 

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\dot{M}_{\mathrm{wind}}=2.0\times10^{-9}\,\mathrm{M_{\sun}\, yr^{-1}}$
\end_inset 

.
 The temperature of the magentosphere is relatively high compared to the
 standard cases (e.g.\SpecialChar ~
Figure\SpecialChar ~

\begin_inset LatexCommand \ref{fig:atlas_acc_models}

\end_inset 

; also 
\begin_inset ERT
status Collapsed

\layout Standard

\backslash 
citealt{muzerolle:2001}
